In this project, you need to configure the API URL, endpoint, and the JSON output location in the script file.

When you run the script:
node scripts/fetch-api-data.js

the script will call the configured API and automatically create/update the JSON file with the latest API response.

If the API returns a valid response, the JSON file will be updated with the new data. If the API does not return a response or the request fails, the existing JSON file will remain unchanged, preserving the previously stored data.





intha project la api url ah script file la endpoints kulla pass panitu json location add panna athu direct ah json file create panni athula api response ah store pannirum

Script ah run panna command

node scripts/fetch-api-data.js

oru time trigger panna script api la response vantha atha store pannum illana prev json data va remove pannathu old data apdiye irukum



